subclause.text:
the drug is classified, for purposes of
				applying tiered copayments consistent with section 1860D–2(b)(2)(B), in the
				highest copayment tier (such as a tier 4 for specialty brand-name drugs);

takes title to the drugs and distributes
				the drugs to eligible part D individuals free or at nominal charge on the basis
				of the entity’s assessment of financial need of such individuals;
